<item>
            <title>[LU-13479] &quot;could not allocate data integrity bioset&quot; on centos7</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13479</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When large discard bio issued to devices support block integrity,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a&#160;&quot;could not allocate data integrity bioset&quot; kernel message will be displayed and the discard bio will end with EIO.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we should only enable integrity for bio when it&apos;s a read/write bio, this ticket tracks backporting of upstream kernel patch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
